Here are examples of the code changes needed to fix the session and credential issues when hosted:

**login.tsx**

Send credentials on login request:

```js
const response = await fetch('/login', {
  credentials: 'include' 
});
```

Force refresh user data after login:

```js 
const { data } = await login({
  variables: {
    email,
    password
  }
});

getUserData();
```

**UserContext.tsx** 

Memoize user data:

```js
const { data, loading } = useQuery(GET_CURRENT_USER, {
  // Only fetch if not already loaded
  skip: !!userData 
});

useEffect(() => {
  if(data) {
    setUserData(data);
  }
}, [data]);
```

Handle null user:

```js
if(!userData) {
  logout();
  router.push('/login'); 
}
```

**AuthGuard.tsx**

Check loading state:

```jsx
if(loading) {
  return <p>Loading...</p>;
}

if(!userData?.me) {
  return <Navigate to="/login" />; 
}
```

**app.ts**

Session middleware first:

```js
// Session 
app.use(session({..}));

// Routes
app.post('/login', ...);
```

**server.ts** 

Enable CORS:

```js
const server = new ApolloServer({
  cors: {
    origin: 'https://frontend.com',
    credentials: true 
  }
});
```

Memoize User model:

```js
