Taking another look at the server.ts and app.ts files for your backend, here are a few things to check that could help with getting sessions working properly in production when hosted:

In server.ts:

- Enable CORS credentials when creating ApolloServer:

```js
const server = new ApolloServer({
  cors: {
    origin: 'https://yourfrontend.com',
    credentials: true 
  }
})
```

- Make sure Apollo middleware is applied before other app routes:

```js
server.applyMiddleware({ app }); 

// Other routes
app.post('/login', ...);
```

In app.ts:

- Set the session cookie to be secure when in production:

```js 
if (process.env.NODE_ENV === 'production') {
  sessionConfig.cookie.secure = true; 
}
```

- Configure the session store for production - using something like Redis rather than default memory store:

```js
const RedisStore = require('connect-redis')(session);
const redisClient = redis.createClient(REDIS_URL);

app.use(session({
  store: new RedisStore({client: redisClient}),
  ...
}))
```

- Make sure session middleware comes before other app routes

These changes should ensure credentials and CORS are properly handled for sessions in production. Let me know if you have any other questions!

You're right, my apologies. Since you are using MongoStore for your sessions and not the default memory store, some of my previous suggestions about configuring Redis would not apply directly.

With MongoStore, here are a few key things to double check for getting sessions working properly in production when hosted:

- In server.ts, still enable CORS credentials in ApolloServer:

```js
const server = new ApolloServer({
  cors: {
    origin: 'https://yourfrontend.com',
    credentials: true
  }  
});
```

- In app.ts, configure the MongoStore for production:

```js
const mongoStore = MongoStore.create({
  mongoUrl: process.env.MONGO_URI,
  autoRemove: 'native' // Handles expired sessions
});

app.use(session({
  store: mongoStore,
  ...
}));
```

- Set the cookie to be secure in production:

```js
if (process.env.NODE_ENV === 'production') {
  sessionConfig.cookie.secure = true;
}
```

- Make sure session middleware comes before routes

- On login, call `req.session.save()` to persist session

The main things are enabling CORS credentials, configuring MongoStore for production, and ensuring the session is saved on login.

Let me know if you have any other questions!
